- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper uses a Boltzmann machine, a type of graphical model commonly used in machine learning, to model the sparsity pattern. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): The paper demonstrates the effectiveness of the proposed approach on real-life signals, which are patches of natural images. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks): The paper mentions a special case where the dependency model corresponds to a certain sparse graph, which is a topic commonly studied in social and information networks.
